@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

@{MS "Introduction"}

You all know PDAs where you can draw lines with a pen on the display and the
PDA is converting these combinations into characters or functions.@{par}

Meridian is doing exactly this! Meridian is a small commodity to create virtual hotkeys by using the
mouse. You paint a square and Meridian is starting the requested action.
Since the starting point and the direction is also important, there are countless
combinations you can use.@{par}

I promise, you'll love it. Flip the screen, close a window, quitting requesters, starting programs
and actions just by moving the mouse. No visible GUI, dock or something like that. Just the mouse
pointer on the screen. I am using Meridian now for around 24 hours and I can't live without it
anymore.@{par}

@endnode
@node "Systemrequirements" "Systemrequirements"

@{MS "System requirements"}

Meridian (should work) works on all Amigas with OS 2.0 or higher.
Some features require OS3.0 or up!@{par}

@endnode
@node "Featurelist" "Features"

@{MS "Features"}

░ Commodity@{par}

░ Easy configuration@{par}

░ Online Help@{par}

░ Locale Support@{par}

@endnode
