@node "HowToInstall" "Installation"

@{MS "Installation"}

Just use the included installer script to install this application!@{par}

@{b}Don't try to install this archive by hand, because this may cause many trouble. The automatic installation
ensures a minimum use of disc and memory space!@{ub}

@endnode
@node "QuickStart" "How to use Meridian"

@{MS "How to use Meridian"}

After installation perform a reboot or start @{b}MeridianServer@{ub} by clicking on it's icon.@{par}

Now start @{b}Meridian@{ub} and a window with listview appears.

@{MT "Step 1"}

Open the @{"Global Set-Up" link "Glob"} window and specify a qualifier of your
choice. The middle mouse button is default.@{par}


@{MT "Step 2"}

Back in the main window @{b}select new@{ub} and you'll see the
@{"Meridian Set-Up" link "Edit"} window. In the left upper corner there is a small empty
box. This is where your @{"meridian" link "FAQSMeridian"} is displayed as vector
arrows. Below the name gadget there is a long status display. Here is a
@{"small picture" link "/pictures/Step2.ilbm/main"} of the whole window.@{par}

@image "/Pictures/Step2.ilbm"

@{MT "Step 3"}

Press and @{b}hold@{ub} the qualifier and move the mouse straight up and to the right and release the qualifier. The window
should look like displayed in this @{"image" link "/pictures/Step3.ilbm/main"}.@{par}

Try to make figures and then try to copy them. Get a feeling for the handling and the usage.@{par}

@image "/Pictures/Step3.ilbm"

@{MT "Step 4"}

Specify a name, and execution type and the command you want to be executed for
this meridian. The @{"example picture" link "/pictures/Step4.ilbm/main"} shows
how to create a CD-Tray Eject/Load. Meridian is opening and closing the cd tray
each time you "paint" this meridian with the qualifier pressed.@{par}

@image "/Pictures/Step4.ilbm"

@{MT "Step 5"}

Press the use gadget and you'll return to the main window. Save the meridian
preferences to disk. Now the commodity is active again. Use the Qualifier and
move the mouse like you've done in @{b}step 3@{ub} and your cd drive should
react.@{par}

@endnode
