@node "Buglist" "Bug List"

@{MS "Bug List"}

When using MagicMenu it's possible to freeze the system. This always happens when using the
right mouse button as qualifier. Using any other qualifier disables the problem. Meridian
is using always using the same code for operation so the problem must be MagicMenu. The right
button is normally for menu usage, which indicates the problem is within MagicMenu V2.35.@{par}

@{MT "MorphOS 1.4 Related Problems"}

The macro WindowClose isn't working. This is a compatibly problem
with the MorphOS input.device. Currently there isn't anything I can do.@{par}

The @{"key command" link "EditComm"} feature isn't working correct on MorphOS.
This is also a compatibly problem of the input.device, which does not create a
press/release. In fact it's just creating a pressed event, which causes endless
running characters. Currently there is no way around.@{par}

@endnode
